[2] Sierra Leone: 5th contact case
Date: Fri 11 Sep 2015
Source: Xinhuanet [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2015-09/12/c_134616229.htm


Sierra Leone records 5th Ebola case
---------------------------------
The National Ebola Response Center (NERC) of Sierra Leone reported on Fri [11 Sep 2015] another case positive for Ebola virus disease [EVD] in the Sellakafter village in Kambia district, north of Sierra Leone.

This brings the number of people who have been infected with the disease to 5 for the past week. Disclosing this to Xinhua in a telephone interview, the Communication Officer and spokesman for NERC, Sidi Yayah Tunis, said all the cases are relatives of the 67-year-old woman who died of [EVD] about 2 weeks ago in the village.

Tunis explained that "the victim was among a number of high risk cases quarantined in the village" and "took part in the washing and burial of the late lady." Tunis pointed out that one good thing is that "all the infected people are coming from those under quarantine and not outside the quarantine home."

The CEO of NERC, Palo Conteh told a local radio station that the new cases could be attributed to "stubbornness on the part of the relatives who failed to report to the appropriate authorities until it was very late."

He spoke of the proactiveness of the district EVD team in [locating] the lady when she died and was proved positive for [EVD] before she was buried.

He warned all business houses and restaurants that those who do not conform to the Ebola restrictions will be shut down and remain shut down until the end of Ebola epidemic.

Sierra Leone is now in the 15th month in the fight against [EVD] much as "we are winning the war, but the fight is daunting and tough," said Palo Conteh.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The fact that these 5 cases are all relatives of the index case bodes well for the termination of Ebola virus transmission in this last chain of contacts. It suggests the virus is currently not spreading by means other than direct contact. - Mod.LK]

