10 Sep 2015 Liberia: Teachers warned against stigmatizing Ebola survivors
http://www.gnnliberia.com/articles/2015/09/10/liberia-teachers-warned-against-stigmatizing-ebola-survivors
[Teachers in Grand Cape Mount County have been warned against stigmatizing students who are Ebola virus disease [EVD] survivors and urged to rather encourage them to pursue their education. The warning was sounded by the County Education Officer, Dwight Harvey, in his remarks on Tue [8 Sep 2015] at the official opening of a 6-day Teachers Training Workshop in Robertsport organized by the Ministry of Education (MOE) with funding from UNICEF [United Nations International Children's Emergency Fund]. Harvey said stigmatizing students who are Ebola survivors could make them drop out of school and render their future bleak. The Liberian educator noted that if teachers stigmatize children, it could create psychological problems for them...more]

